<b>Subject:</b> Prediction<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=681" TARGET=_self>TOPIC: POLICING OURSELVES WITH NO LVL LIMIT</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>There will be small bands comprised of or led by knowledgeable testers (read: Phase 3 or earlier) that will be able to go in and take over zones, per se, preventing others from gaining nice, juicy exp. Imagine how a small group of level 5's (with healing abilities within the group) would be able to hold the bottleneck from Qeynos Hills to Blackburrow while their buddies are mining the top level(BB). After a set period of time, they switch until both halves of the group are ready to move on to the next higher level bottleneck....

<P>*shudder*
<BR>*grin*
<P>People best make friends FAST or suffer the consequences....
<P>Look forward to working with you Geiger. PvP has become MY top priority...(after general pre-customer support, of course :)
<P>Zariin
<P>&gt; The server as far as I know will have no PvP LvL cap. This will
<BR>&gt; make a need for us to police our own: What are our Options?
<BR>&gt; Rather than lead into this one I'd like people to spew as many
<BR>&gt; ideas as possible.
<BR>
